{"type":"message","id":"5513b0f7","parentId":"3c770df9","timestamp":"2026-05-11T05:11:52.465Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is clarifying what they want. It seems like they want a Vegas scanning tool - but not a timed/scheduled scan. They want it on-demand, maybe when they ask for it. And the previous message context shows a MCHP trade signal that was sent before.\n\nThe user's message \"Vegas 不用定時掃描\" means \"Vegas [ scanning ] doesn't need scheduled scanning\" - they want to run it manually on demand, not on a schedule.\n\nAnd \"串yfinance 或永豐api\" means they want it connected to yfinance or Shioaji (Shuang-Yong/.sinopac API).\n\nSo the pipeline would be:\n1. Get list of ~500 Taiwan stocks\n\n\n2. Pull data via yfinance or Shioaji\n3. Compute Vegas tunnel EMA levels (EMA144/169 for the tunnel and EMA576/676 for the longer trend)\n4. Filter for signals where price breaks through the tunnel with EMA12 confirmation, combined with strong trend alignment\n5. Output the results as a scan report\n\nI'm building a Python tool that fetches Taiwan stock data, calculates the necessary EMAs, applies the Vegas tunnel filtering logic, and generates an on-demand report without any scheduled execution.\n","thinkingSignature":"73495b1bdc7e5a9da10fb73904fe4a870a486ac3d8adcea69989344863881599"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n收到！**隨選掃描**模式，不要排程。搞一個 `vegas_scan.py`，yfinance + Shioaji 都能用，Jo 要掃的時候手動執行就好。\n\n先問一下偏好：\n1. **yfinance**（免安裝，國外券商資料，但台股資料較少/延遲）\n2. **Shioaji（永豐金）**（需要證券帳戶，資料完整即時，涵蓋台股上市櫃）\n\n你用哪個？如果有在用永豐金的話果建議直接走 Shioaji，台股資料庫比較完整。📈"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":46522,"output":387,"cacheRead":64,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46973,"cost":{"input":0.0139566,"output":0.00046439999999999996,"cacheRead":0.00000384,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01442484}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778476289910,"responseId":"065098046034b6540da98cc373ecdf74"}}
