{"type":"message","id":"9fc4338e","parentId":"fd5bf1ef","timestamp":"2026-05-11T05:28:19.199Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The edit tool is not accepting my format. Let me just use write to overwrite the file with the correct credentials. Actually wait - let me look at the edit tool schema more carefully.\n\nThe `edit` tool takes:\n```\n{\n  \"path\": string,\n  \"edits\": [\n    {\n      \"oldText\": string,\n      \"newText\": string\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nBut I'm passing `{\"oldText\": \"...\", \"newText\": \"...\", \"path\": \"...\", \"edits\": [...]}` - I'm mixing up the top-level `path` param with the edits structure.\n\nActually looking at the error: `\"edits\": [{\"newText\": \"...\", \"oldText\": \"...\"}]` - it says `edits[0]` must be object. \n\nThe object has `newText` and `oldText` which look right, but maybe the issue is that I'm using `oldText` instead of the correct field name like `old_text`? Let me re-read the edit tool description:\n\n\"Each edit is matched against the original file, not incrementally. If two changes touch the same block or nearby lines, merge them into one edit instead of emitting overlapping edits.\"\n\nAnd in the params:\n- edis[].oldText: Exact text for one targeted replacement. Must match unique, non-overlapping region of original.\n- edis[].newText: Replacement text for this targeted edit.\n\nSo the format should be:\n```json\n{\n  \"path\": \"...\",\n  \"edits\": [\n    {\"oldText\": \"....\", \"newText\": \"...\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nThat looks right. But the error says `\"edits[0]\": must be object`. Maybe the issue is the `\\` in my oldText? No, that shouldn't matter in JSON.\n\nWait, the error message actually shows the edits array is being parsed correctly with the newText and oldText fields, so the format itself is fine. The real problem might be that the edits array is being interpreted as a string somewhere in the parsing - perhaps the JSON is being double-serialized or something is treating the entire edits parameter as a string rather than an array. That's a different schema issue. Let me try wrapping it in a list or checking if edits should be a dict instead. Actually, let me just use exec to do a targeted string replacement in the file - that's simpler than wrestling with the edit tool format.\n","thinkingSignature":"2f45e0438e1805cbbb1a39473508fb4f36b5de2000ab0cdc2756c63899aae469"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_c4r3c68gmwww_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray; python -c \"\ncontent = open('vegas_scan.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8').read()\ncontent = content.replace('API_KEY = \\\"YOUR_API_KEY\\\"', 'API_KEY = \\\"FCcefW9iatHvYyp3XgSYVM1VhdmZMawjQ49Mzp97WPBF\\\"')\ncontent = content.replace('API_SECRET = \\\"YOUR_API_SECRET\\\"', 'API_SECRET = \\\"3r6UGMUX7bnxhnbrZ92sSseGVzL3C63kkBxH3WkAPsgW\\\"')\nopen('vegas_scan.py', 'w', encoding='utf-8').write(content)\nprint('✅ 已更新 API Key')\n\"","timeout":"10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":374,"output":694,"cacheRead":50368,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":51436,"cost":{"input":0.00011219999999999999,"output":0.0008328,"cacheRead":0.00302208,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0039670799999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778477278206,"responseId":"06509be0e5ba403b1d6a49d3e188b836"}}
