{"type":"message","id":"36ecffc0","parentId":"3d866df1","timestamp":"2026-05-11T09:22:06.340Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is cp950 codec for Chinese characters. But the count itself showed 15 lines. Wait - actually the \"lines\" here are lines of the array definition, not stock codes. The array is all on 15 lines but contains many stock codes.\n\nLet me count the actual stock codes properly. Each line in the array has multiple stock codes separated by commas. The problem is my check_list.py script counts the array lines (15), not the stock codes.\n\nLet me fix it to count stock codes properly.\n","thinkingSignature":"9f4b484303dbc75871fe998a5b48c13632dda3c5c2ad5c093c8d0d3752a5f973"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vyr50iiitnu8_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"with open('vegas_scan.py', 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nstart = content.find('TSE_TOP500')\nend = content.find(']', start)\nsection = content[start:end+1]\n\n# Extract stock codes (strings with 4 digits)\nimport re\ncodes = re.findall(r'\"(\\d{4})\"', section)\nprint(f'Total stock codes: {len(codes)}')\nprint(f'Target: 500')\nprint()\nif len(codes) < 500:\n    print(f'⚠️  目前只有 {len(codes)} 檔，需要補齊到 500 檔')\nprint()\nprint('First 10:', codes[:10])\nprint('Last 5:', codes[-5:])","path":"C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\agents\\ray\\check_list.py"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":641,"output":315,"cacheRead":57920,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58876,"cost":{"input":0.00019229999999999999,"output":0.00037799999999999997,"cacheRead":0.0034752,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0040455}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778491308158,"responseId":"0650d2ac083dbdd28adfeebc4bec6801"}}
