{"type":"message","id":"d8eb62b7","parentId":"72ca29e0","timestamp":"2026-05-11T09:28:49.887Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `__init__.py` uses `from FinMind import ...` but the actual package is lowercase `finmind`. This is a case-sensitivity issue on Windows - the directory is `finmind` but the import is trying to import `FinMind`. Let me check if there's a `FinMind` directory or if this is a case issue.\n\nActually, looking at the directory listing, the files are lowercase (`_version.py`, `__init__.py`). But the `__init__.py` does `from FinMind import ...` which would look for a `FinMind` package directory (capital F). On Windows, the file system is case-insensitive, but Python import is case-sensitive. \n\nThe package is installed as lowercase `finmind` but the code is trying to import `FinMind`, which would fail on any case-sensitive filesystem. Since Python imports are case-sensitive regardless of the OS, this should be failing - but if it's actually working on this Windows system, the directory name must somehow match what Python is looking for.\n\nLet me check the actual `site-packages` directory to see what directories exist there, since the earlier output showed `finmind` in lowercase but that contradicts the import attempting `FinMind`.\n","thinkingSignature":"b4794e911133f75c56311481f89eb605fcc0127e7ceafc8421f0ccb440853f76"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_i1e6g8up46lk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"dir \"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\Lib\\site-packages\" | findstr -i \"finmind\"","timeout":"10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":145,"output":315,"cacheRead":66112,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66572,"cost":{"input":0.0000435,"output":0.00037799999999999997,"cacheRead":0.00396672,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00438822}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778491696784,"responseId":"0650d4316c654d4c4175b4a445d2b41