{"type":"message","id":"04538e4f","parentId":"07019c70","timestamp":"2026-05-11T09:35:13.720Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, yfinance is available. Now let me write a comprehensive updated vegas_scan.py that includes:\n\n1. **US Markets** (via yfinance, real-time):\n   - S&P 500 (~500 stocks)\n   - NASDAQ 100 (~100 stocks)\n   - SOX (Philadelphia Semiconductor Index ~30 stocks)\n   \n2. **Taiwan Market** (via Shioaji primary / yfinance backup):\n   - TWSE 500 (上市股票市值前 500)\n\nThe script will be modular, allowing scanning of any market independently. Let me write this comprehensive update.\n\nFor S&P 500 - I can use yfinance's tickers directly or fetch from a source.\n\n\nNASDAQ 100 is available as a preset in yfinance with .NASDAQ100 tickers, and SOX components can be hardcoded since there are only about 30 of them. For TWSE 500, I'll attempt Shioaji first and fall back to yfinance for Taiwan stocks if needed. Let me build out the full implementation now.\n","thinkingSignature":"a946503cd48c608e0342f184650f0038b409e97ba27da57f4fb6ba0d1e3eb182"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_xm85cwfvb908_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe -c \"\nimport yfinance as yf\n# Test yfinance can fetch US stock\nt = yf.Ticker('AAPL')\nh = t.history(period='5d')\nprint('AAPL recent close:', h['Close'].iloc[-1] if len(h) > 0 else 'no data')\nprint('yfinance US data OK')\n\" 2>&1","timeout":"30","yieldMs":"25000"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":153,"output":351,"cacheRead":75008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":75512,"cost":{"input":0.0000459,"output":0.0004212,"cacheRead":0.004500479999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.004967579999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778492081899,"responseId":"0650d5b2eb9438d3dbf68bb5ce90f1e4"}}
