{"type":"message","id":"80c7c4c0","parentId":"136ac507","timestamp":"2026-05-11T09:55:37.760Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the timestamp unit - it's nanoseconds. Let me now check what the daily data looks like and test the Vegas scan with Shioaji.\n\nNow let me update the vegas_scan.py to:\n1. Use the correct Shioaji credentials (api_key and secret_key)\n2. Use Shioaji for TWSE data (instead of FinMind as primary)\n3. Keep yfinance for US stocks\n\nActually, Shioaji's kbars gives minute-level data by default. For daily scanning I need to either:\n1. Use the `api.kbars` with daily interval somehow\n2. Or use FinMind for daily data and Shioaji for real-time\n\n\n3. \nLooking at Shioaji's kbars documentation, it returns tick data by default, not daily. I need to figure out how to aggregate this to daily OHLCV data for the scan. The most practical approach is to stick with FinMind for daily data since it's designed for this, and keep Shioaji's real-time capabilities separate for later use.\n\nFor now, I'll update vegas_scan.py to use the correct Shioaji credentials while keeping FinMind as the primary data source for daily prices, with yfinance as a backup option.\n\nActually, Shioaji does have a method to get daily K-bars by specifying the timeframe parameter. Let me verify that approach first before making changes. The key is finding the right Shioaji method for daily data aggregation rather than switching entirely between APIs.\n","thinkingSignature":"9eeb959916290ae4bfb01668a690bcadbd3fa969dfcc2d9ccd69c15890c80c34"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_dpug8cmoqn4s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\python.exe -c \"\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, r'C:\\Users\\USER\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\\Python\\Python312\\Lib\\site-packages')\nimport shioaji as sj\nimport inspect\n\n# Check kbars signature\nsig = inspect.signature(sj.SolaceAPI.kbars