{"type":"message","id":"5b101134","parentId":"9e889a90","timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:44:07.628Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the ENTG signal message, I notice it's sent as a direct message to Jo in response to a cron job response. But the ENTG signal itself doesn't match any existing cron job in the list.\n\nLet me look at the cron jobs more carefully:\n- `d824a2bb` - \"Tina 自主決策五大層\" every 3 hours\n- `6263e6d0` - \"Leo v6.5 科技股波段\" at 8,11,14,17,21 on weekdays\n- `9dcfa4d6` - \"Vegas Tunnel TW 每日掃描\" at 16:30 on weekdays (this is mine!)\n\n\n- `d8fe08ae` - \"US AI Tech 每日分析\" at 8:30 on weekdays\n- `56da375e` - \"US Margin 每日分析\" at 18:00 on weekdays\n\nNone of these cron jobs appear to have produced the ENTG message, and it's not the Vegas Tunnel scan either since that runs at 16:30 while the ENTG was sent much later in the evening.\n\nLooking back at the cron list, the ENTG signal is actually coming from the Leo v6.5 job that runs on weekdays at 8, 11, 14, 17, and 21 — that's the only one that matches the timing. I found it—the Leo v6.5 cron job at 17:00 is the source of that ENTG signal, and it runs a script located at `C:\\Users\\USER\\.openclaw\\workspace\\Tina_Quant_System\\teams\\leadtrades\\leos\\leos_v65.py`. I can confirm the schedule matches perfectly with the trading times, so that afternoon slot at 17:00 aligns with the market hours. The cron expression `0 8,11,14,17,21 * * 1-5` creates five scheduled runs across US market hours that correspond to the times displayed in the signal (UTC+8).\n","thinkingSignature":"5b72d451ae88d2f831c21eeb5a2b7f449fa5f8cd2a7ea21734c3a53006b9bf40"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了。\n\n這個訊號不是來自 `vegas_scan.py`，而是來自另一個已存在的排程：\n\n---\n\n## 🔍 訊號來源\n\n| 項目 | 內容 |\n|------|------|\n| **Job 名稱** | `Leo v6.5 科技股波段（分散排程）` |\n| **執行腳本** | `le...le\\leos_v65.py` |\n| **排程** | `0 8,11,14,17,21 * * 1-5`（台股交易日每天5次）|\n| **Agent** | `tina-reports` |\n\n---\n\n## ⏰ 對照時間\n\n訊號顯示的時間和 `17:00