{"type":"message","id":"86b27be6","parentId":"23e3c91a","timestamp":"2026-05-11T10:54:37.949Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The log doesn't show the main progress output (stock counts, etc.). The TWSE scan might be stuck at the first 50 stocks, or there's something going on. \n\nLooking at the output more carefully - those 404 errors are for `.TWO` tickers (Taipei exchange OTC). The TWSE scan is proceeding and just outputting errors to stderr (which is expected for delisted stocks).\n\nBut I don't see any `[SCAN]` or `[FETCH]` messages in the log. This is strange. Let me look at the code - it should print \"Fetching stock lists\" etc. \n\nWait - the \"HTTP Error 404\" messages are stderr output from PowerShell. \n\nThe Python script is outputting to stderr while the main stdout might be buffered or still in progress, or the script could be stuck. I should probably kill this process and add progress logging, then run it in the background to monitor output as it comes.\n","thinkingSignature":"d7f1dc1e82a565d7a3fd2aca65d183fb98f4634d8f75e68f50b1f57061f27505"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p4avweu691o8_1","name":"process","arguments":{"action":"kill","sessionId":"kind-shore"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":358,"output":228,"cacheRead":117056,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":117642,"cost":{"input":0.0001074,"output":0.0002736,"cacheRead":0.007023359999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00740436}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1778496842870,"responseId":"0650e85fe164fd5aaa0182e24592d626"}}
